# New topic: sandbox → practice lesson → Mongo → registries → visualization

Use this when a developer has iterated on **`main.go`** (or a small runnable) under **`sandbox/<lab>/<topic>/`** and wants a full **TraceLab concept**: downloadable practice, editor **`codeFiles`**, optional **simulation**, and curriculum wiring.

Path examples: **`sandbox/system-design/load-balancer/`** (topic folder name is usually short; URL slug may differ, e.g. **`load-balancing`**).

---

## Files you will touch (every new topic)

This is the **complete list** of files that change for a typical new topic. Use it as a checklist:

| Area | File(s) | What you do |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **Sandbox** | `sandbox/<lab>/<topic>/go.mod`, `main.go`, `main_test.go`, `solution.go`, `present.go`, `bad.go`, `LAB.md` | Create the practice bundle (§1). |
| **Practice → Mongo** | *(command only)* | **`make sync-sandbox-mongo`** with **`SANDBOX`**, **`CONCEPT`**, **`ZIP`**, **`FOLDER`**, **`FILES`** (see **`README.md`**), or **`go run ./cmd/sync-sandbox-practice`** with the same values as flags. No per-topic binaries or Makefile targets. |
| **Lesson panel** | `apps/web/src/components/lessons/<lab>/<Topic>Lesson.tsx` | New text-lesson component (`LessonRoot` / `LessonProblem` / `LessonDiagram` / `LessonTradeoffs`). |
| **Lesson registry** | `apps/web/src/features/lessons/lessonRegistry.ts` | Import + register `"<slug>": <Topic>Lesson`. |
| **Simulation** | `apps/web/src/components/simulations/<lab>/<Topic>Simulation.tsx` + `.module.css` | SVG sim matching the user's PNG; reuse `CachingSimulation.module.css` panel chrome; rAF packet animation; `onMetrics` emitting metric ids. |
| **Viz registry** | `apps/web/src/features/concepts/vizRegistry.tsx` | Thin adapter (`VizComponent`) + `VIZ_REGISTRY['<vizType>']` entry. |
| **Detail page** | `apps/web/src/features/concepts/pages/ConceptDetailPage.tsx` | Only if a new `practice.folder` fallback is needed in `resolveVizComponent`; otherwise **no change**. |
| **API** | `services/api/internal/catalog/handler.go` | Only if new `normalizeCodeFilesForLesson` edge cases appear; otherwise **no change**. |
| **SPA types** | `apps/web/src/types/labConcept.ts` | Only if new fields are added to the lesson payload; otherwise **no change**. |
| **Code panel** | `apps/web/src/components/code/DynamicCodePanel.tsx` | Only if new lang/content fallback rules; otherwise **no change**. |
| **Mongo** | `Labs` doc (concepts[] row + navSections item), `Concepts` doc (_id, vizType, codeFiles, parameters, metricGroups) | Manual or via one-off script (delete after). |
| **README** | `sandbox/README.md` | Document the new sandbox path if useful; practice sync stays generic (**`make sync-sandbox-mongo`**). |

Items marked **"no change"** are already generic enough from previous topics. The first six rows are always new files or edits (practice sync is a command, not a new file).

---

## 1. Practice bundle (under `sandbox/<lab>/<topic>/`)

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| **`go.mod`** | Small module (e.g. `module <topic>-practice`, matching Go version). |
| **`main.go`** | **Student starter**: `func main()`, types/API to implement, **`TODO`s**. Must pass **`go test ./...`** when solved (no long-running servers in default test build). |
| **`main_test.go`** | Tests for the **testable core** only (pure logic; no binding ports in tests). |
| **`solution.go`** | **`//go:build ignore`** at top; full solution, **same API as `main.go`**. Must be **test-valid by definition** (see below). |
| **`present.go`** | **`//go:build ignore`**: idiomatic “good” code — typically evolved from the prototype **`main.go`** you were happy with. Runnable with **`go run present.go`**. |
| **`bad.go`** | **`//go:build ignore`**: one clear anti-pattern or wrong approach; same rough shape as **`present.go`** so comparison teaches. **`go run bad.go`**. |
| **`LAB.md`** | Goals, file table, **`go test` / `go run`** commands, pointers to **`present`** vs **`bad`**. |

### Editor `codeFiles` vs ZIP

- **`Concepts` / `Labs`** **`codeFiles`** (Implementation panel) should expose **read-only teaching slices**: usually **`present.go`** and **`bad.go`** with optional **`role`**: `present` / `bad`.
- The working **`main.go`** (starter) lives in the **practice ZIP** (`practice.files`), not merged into **`codeFiles`** for editing in the same way — see **`DynamicCodePanel`** + API **`normalizeCodeFilesForLesson`**.
- Practically: once **`main.go`** is stable as the student exercise, **copy/refine that logic into `present.go`** for the “good” reference; **`bad.go`** is a deliberate broken variant.

### `solution.go` and `main_test.go` (required invariant)

**`solution.go` must pass the lesson tests by construction:** if you take the solution body (everything that belongs in the student file — types, functions, **`main`** as needed) and **paste it into `main.go`** in place of the starter stubs, then **`go test ./...`** must pass. The reference implementation and **`main_test.go`** must stay in lockstep: same exported/unexported surface the tests exercise, no extra manual steps. Keep **`//go:build ignore`** on **`solution.go`** so the default package build stays the student **`main.go`**.

### HTTP / servers

Extract a **small testable API** into **`main.go`** / tests; keep servers or demos in **`present.go`** so **`go test ./...`** stays hermetic.

