## 3. Syncing to Mongo

### A. Practice ZIP + `practice` field

Use **`make sync-sandbox-mongo`** (repo root, **`.env`** as needed) or **`go run ./cmd/sync-sandbox-practice`** to **`$set`** **`practice`** (`zipName`, `folder`, `files[]`) on **`Concepts._id`**. Variables / flags: **`SANDBOX`** / **`-sandbox`**, **`CONCEPT`** / **`-concept`**, **`ZIP`** / **`-zip`**, **`FOLDER`** / **`-folder`**, **`FILES`** / **`-files`**, plus **`-repo`** when using **`go run`** (repo root path).

- **`-files`** order is the ZIP contents; include **`go.mod`**, **`LAB.md`**, **`main.go`**, **`main_test.go`**, **`solution.go`**, **`present.go`**, **`bad.go`** as needed.

There is **only** **`cmd/sync-sandbox-practice`** for this — no **`sync-*-practice`** per topic.

### B. One-off metadata (`parameters`, `vizType`, `metricGroups`, …)

For first-time wiring, a **temporary** helper is fine: small **`go run`** (Mongo update), **`mongosh`**, or a throwaway script that **`$set`s** the fields on **`Concepts`** (and **`Labs.concepts[]`** row if you keep catalog there).

**After values are correct in the database, remove** any **throwaway** Mongo-update script. **`sync-sandbox-practice`** stays in the repo as the single practice sync entry.

