## 4. `lessonRegistry` (text panel)

In **`apps/web/src/features/lessons/lessonRegistry.ts`**, map **`slug` → component** for concepts whose **`vizType`** is **`lesson`**, empty, or not a registered sim (see **`resolveLessonPanelComponent`** in **`ConceptDetailPage.tsx`**).

- Slug **must match** **`Labs.concepts[].slug`** and **`/concept/<slug>`**.

---

## 5. Visualization + `vizRegistry`

The user provides a **PNG (or sketch) of the architecture flow**. This is the primary design input for the simulation SVG.

1. **Study the PNG**: identify nodes (boxes), edges (arrows / dashed lines), request flow direction, and any labels. The SVG must reproduce this layout — same node count, same topology, same labeling style.
2. **Implement** under **`apps/web/src/components/simulations/<lab>/`**:
   - Wrap in the **Architecture Visualizer** panel header (reuse **`CachingSimulation.module.css`** panel chrome — header with **READY / SIMULATION LIVE** dot + **EXECUTE SIMULATION / STOP** button). See **`CachingSimulation.tsx`** and **`LoadBalancerRoundRobinSimulation.tsx`** as references.
   - Animate **request packets** (small glowing circles via `requestAnimationFrame`) traveling the edges in the SVG, matching the flow shown in the PNG.
   - Emit **`onMetrics`** with string values keyed to the **`metricGroups`** ids defined in step 2.
3. **Register** in **`apps/web/src/features/concepts/vizRegistry.tsx`**:
   - Add a thin **`VizComponent`** adapter that maps **`paramValues`** → sim props and stringifies **`onMetrics`**.
   - **`VIZ_REGISTRY[vizType]`** key must match **`vizType`** in Mongo (or use **`practice.folder`** special cases in **`resolveVizComponent`**).
4. **Set `vizType`** on the concept to that registry key (e.g. **`load-balancer`**). If **`Concepts`** overrides **`Labs`**, ensure **`Concepts`** does not leave **`vizType`** as **`""`** if it would wipe a good value from **`Labs`**.

---

## 6. Curriculum checklist

- **`Labs`** document: **`concepts[]`** row (**`slug`**, **`title`**, **`status`**, **`labKind`**, **`vizType`**, **`codeFiles`** names/roles as needed).
- **`navSections`**: item **`slug`** equals concept **`slug`** for a working sidebar link.
- **`Concepts._id`**: `"<labId>/<slug>"` for merged detail + **`practice`**.
- Practice sync is always **`make sync-sandbox-mongo`** / **`sync-sandbox-practice`** — no new Makefile targets for each lab.

---

## Prompt snippet for the agent

> I have a working **`main.go`** under **`sandbox/<lab>/<topic>/`**. Here is a PNG of the architecture flow I want the simulation to match: *(attach PNG)*.
>
> 1. Turn the sandbox into a **practice bundle**: **`go.mod`**, **`main.go`** (student starter with TODOs), **`main_test.go`**, **`solution.go`** (`//go:build ignore` — must pass `go test` when pasted into `main.go`), **`present.go`** (idiomatic demo), **`bad.go`** (anti-pattern), **`LAB.md`**.
> 2. Wire **`sync-sandbox-practice`** for **`Concepts._id` `<labId>/<slug>`**.
> 3. Define **`parameters`** and **`metricGroups`** for the simulation. Metric ids must match what the viz component emits via **`onMetrics`**.
> 4. Build the **SVG simulation** matching the attached PNG — nodes, edges, animated request packets — inside the **Architecture Visualizer** panel header. Register it in **`vizRegistry.tsx`** under **`vizType` `<key>`**.
> 5. Register the **text lesson** panel in **`lessonRegistry.ts`** (slug **`<slug>`**).

Adjust **`<lab>`**, **`<topic>`**, **`<labId>/<slug>`**, **`vizType`**, and sim vs text-only.
